description: The following field definitions make up the shapefile attribute table called School. Each polygon represents a Michigan school district. The attribute table can be found in the file School_d_999v12b.DBF where 999 equals the FIPS county number contained in the file. The FIPS county numbering system uses odd numbers only. The numbers are assigned in alphabetical order. For example, county 001 is Alcona and county 165 is Wexford. The attributes describe the data attached to polygons that represent Michigan school district boundaries as assigned to the Michigan Geographic Framework (MGF).
